{{!--
================================================================================
  TABS — invoke partial: tabs (e.g. tabItems=…)

  Bootstrap 5 tabbed panels: several alternative views on one page, with a
  horizontal tab bar. Only one panel is visible at a time; the active tab uses
  Bootstrap’s `.active` styles so the choice is obvious.

  Requires Bootstrap 5 JS/CSS on the page (wrapper or markdown_wrapper).

  Omit `tabItems`, or pass `[]`: two placeholder tabs render so layout work
  does not need a controller yet.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  CONTEXT FIELDS

  tabsRootId          (optional)  `id` on the outer wrapper. Default: `thaliaTabs`.
                                Change when you put **more than one** tabs block
                                on the same page (each needs a unique id).

  tabsItemIdPrefix    (optional)  Prefix for pane `id`s and tab `data-bs-target`s.
                                Default: `tab` → `#tab-overview`, button
                                `#tab-overview-tab`. Pair with a unique
                                `tabsRootId` when duplicating this partial.

  tabsRootClass       (optional)  Extra classes on the outer wrapper (spacing).
                                Default: `thalia-tabs mb-4`

  tabsNavClass        (optional)  Classes on the `<ul role="tablist">`.
                                Default: `nav nav-tabs`
                                Use `nav nav-pills` for pill-style tabs.

  tabsContentClass    (optional)  Classes on `.tab-content`. Default: (empty)

  tabItems            (optional)  Array of tabs. Each item:

      idSuffix      string   **Unique in the document** (for this prefix), e.g.
                             `"overview"`, `"pricing"`. Used in element ids and
                             `data-bs-target` selectors.

      label         string   Tab button text (plain text; auto-escaped).

      content       string   Panel body HTML. Rendered with `{{{content}}}` —
                             **trusted markup only** (your CMS, server, or
                             designer copy). For untrusted input, fork this
                             partial and use `{{content}}` instead.

      active        optional When truthy, this tab starts selected. Mark **exactly
                             one** item `active: true` (usually the first). If
                             none are marked, no panel has the `show` class until
                             the user clicks a tab.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  NESTING OTHER PARTIALS IN A PANEL

  Prefer building `content` in your controller as HTML strings, or compose in
  the parent template before calling the tabs partial.

  Handlebars does not run nested partials inside a string field; pass finished
  HTML in `content`, or split into separate pages/sections if panels are large.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  EXAMPLE (TypeScript controller → template context)

    const tabItems = [
      {
        idSuffix: 'overview',
        active: true,
        label: 'Overview',
        content:
          '<p class="mb-0">Summary shown by default.</p>',
      },
      {
        idSuffix: 'details',
        label: 'Details',
        content:
          '<p class="mb-0">Longer specification copy.</p>',
      },
      {
        idSuffix: 'downloads',
        label: 'Downloads',
        content:
          '<ul class="mb-0"><li><a href="/files/spec.pdf">Spec (PDF)</a></li></ul>',
      },
    ]

    website.serveHandlebarsTemplate({
      res,
      templatePath: '…/page.hbs',
      data: { title: 'Product', tabItems },
    })

  In the template (inside wrapper content or a partial-block):

    <h1>{{title}}</h1>
    then pass tabItems into the tabs partial.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  ACCESSIBILITY

  • Tab list uses `role="tablist"`; buttons use `role="tab"` with
    `aria-selected` and `aria-controls` (Bootstrap 5 tab plugin).
  • Panels use `role="tabpanel"` and `aria-labelledby` pointing at the tab button.
  • Use stable, readable `idSuffix` values; they appear in URLs/fragments if linked.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  RELATED PARTIALS

  • `faq` — vertical accordion (one open panel), not horizontal tabs.
  • `mermaidCard` + `markdown_processing` — Diagram/Source tabs inside code
    cards only; not for general page content.
================================================================================
--}}
<div class="{{#if tabsRootClass}}{{tabsRootClass}}{{else}}thalia-tabs mb-4{{/if}}"
  id="{{#if tabsRootId}}{{tabsRootId}}{{else}}thaliaTabs{{/if}}">
  <ul class="{{#if tabsNavClass}}{{tabsNavClass}}{{else}}nav nav-tabs{{/if}}" role="tablist">
    {{#each tabItems}}
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button type="button"
          class="nav-link{{#if active}} active{{/if}}"
          id="{{#if ../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{else}}tab{{/if}}-{{idSuffix}}-tab"
          data-bs-toggle="tab"
          data-bs-target="#{{#if ../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{else}}tab{{/if}}-{{idSuffix}}"
          role="tab"
          aria-controls="{{#if ../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{else}}tab{{/if}}-{{idSuffix}}"
          aria-selected="{{#if active}}true{{else}}false{{/if}}">
          {{label}}
        </button>
      </li>
    {{else}}
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button type="button" class="nav-link active" id="tab-sample-1-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab"
          data-bs-target="#tab-sample-1" role="tab" aria-controls="tab-sample-1" aria-selected="true">
          Overview
        </button>
      </li>
      <li class="nav-item" role="presentation">
        <button type="button" class="nav-link" id="tab-sample-2-tab" data-bs-toggle="tab"
          data-bs-target="#tab-sample-2" role="tab" aria-controls="tab-sample-2" aria-selected="false">
          Details
        </button>
      </li>
    {{/each}}
  </ul>
  <div class="tab-content{{#if tabsContentClass}} {{tabsContentClass}}{{/if}}">
    {{#each tabItems}}
      <div
        class="tab-pane fade{{#if active}} show active{{/if}}"
        id="{{#if ../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{else}}tab{{/if}}-{{idSuffix}}"
        role="tabpanel"
        aria-labelledby="{{#if ../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{../tabsItemIdPrefix}}{{else}}tab{{/if}}-{{idSuffix}}-tab"
        tabindex="0">
        {{{content}}}
      </div>
    {{else}}
      <div class="tab-pane fade show active" id="tab-sample-1" role="tabpanel"
        aria-labelledby="tab-sample-1-tab" tabindex="0">
        <p class="mb-0">First placeholder panel. Pass <code>tabItems</code> from your route or controller.
          Each item needs a unique <code>idSuffix</code>, a <code>label</code>, and trusted HTML in
          <code>content</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tab-pane fade" id="tab-sample-2" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-sample-2-tab"
        tabindex="0">
        <p class="mb-0">Second placeholder panel — wire real copy when you are ready.</p>
      </div>
    {{/each}}
  </div>
</div>
